1
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:41,267
Mom, he's abusing Daisy.

2
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:44,100
They need to leave that place
before he hurts Tetay, too.

3
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:45,433
I already know the truth, Mom,

4
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:47,200
about Dad's family
in the Philippines.

5
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:49,733
Why would you make up stories
just to turn me against Dad?

6
00:00:49,867 --> 00:00:52,067
You're so mean!

7
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,133
- I'll kill her!
- Let go of me!

8
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:55,000
Tetay, my dear.

9
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:57,067
We'll take care of this.

10
00:00:58,400 --> 00:00:59,000
Noah!

11
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:00,567
Jeff, help!

12
00:01:00,700 --> 00:01:01,867
Let's bring him to the hospital!

13
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,367
Jessica, listen.

14
00:01:03,500 --> 00:01:05,767
Your mom was just trying
to protect you.

15
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:10,133
Yes, she wronged me and Felma.
But it was for your sake.

16
00:01:10,300 --> 00:01:12,600
Because he wanted you to have
a father.

17
00:01:13,133 --> 00:01:15,233
Dr. Cortes is still doing
the operation.

18
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,100
About what I told you...

19
00:01:17,233 --> 00:01:18,167
That I'll pursue you.

20
00:01:18,300 --> 00:01:19,567
I'm serious about that.

21
00:01:19,700 --> 00:01:21,700
Sis, calm down.

22
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:23,767
Noah's not going to die yet.

23
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:26,167
He still has a mission on earth.

24
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,433
And that is to make you accept
his feelings.

25
00:01:28,567 --> 00:01:30,700
Do you love me, too, Felma?

26
00:01:32,267 --> 00:01:34,467
She said yes already.

27
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,133
We're officially together.

28
00:01:36,267 --> 00:01:38,333
- There you go!
- Oh my!

29
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:42,067
Congratulations, Uncle Noah!

30
00:01:51,867 --> 00:01:53,200
How about you, dear?

31
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:54,600
Bacon.

32
00:01:58,300 --> 00:01:59,933
I'll have some.

33
00:02:01,567 --> 00:02:02,833
Thank you.

34
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:08,167
Ma'am.

35
00:02:12,033 --> 00:02:12,533
Mom.

36
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:14,733
Did you leave Uncle Noah alone?

37
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:17,800
Paz is there.

38
00:02:19,800 --> 00:02:23,400
Jeffrey, Andrea, Didang.

39
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:26,233
Please give Coleen and me
a minute.

40
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,033
Sweetie?

41
00:02:46,533 --> 00:02:47,433
Mom.

42
00:02:48,900 --> 00:02:50,767
I wasn't able to talk to you
last night.

43
00:02:52,633 --> 00:02:56,300
But I noticed that you
weren't happy

44
00:02:57,533 --> 00:03:00,033
that your Uncle Noah and I
became a couple.

45
00:03:00,967 --> 00:03:02,000
Don't you like it?

46
00:03:02,667 --> 00:03:03,433
Mom.

47
00:03:04,567 --> 00:03:06,333
It's not that I don't like it.

48
00:03:08,367 --> 00:03:10,200
I was only hoping that...

49
00:03:11,967 --> 00:03:13,833
when Dad comes back...

50
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:16,600
you would...

51
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:17,633
Sweetie.

52
00:03:18,767 --> 00:03:19,500
Mom.

53
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:21,833
I was just hoping.

54
00:03:22,467 --> 00:03:24,967
I know that it will
never happen.

55
00:03:25,367 --> 00:03:27,233
And I accept that.

56
00:03:28,133 --> 00:03:29,133
And...

57
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,533
Uncle Noah is like a father to
me.

58
00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:36,833
Maybe I was just surprised.

59
00:03:39,733 --> 00:03:40,967
Is it really okay with you?

60
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:44,100
Because if not...

61
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:45,533
Mom!

62
00:03:48,733 --> 00:03:49,900
No.

63
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:52,933
I'm very okay with it, Mom.

64
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:55,533
I want you to be happy.

65
00:03:56,700 --> 00:03:57,400
Yes.

66
00:03:57,833 --> 00:04:00,400
And I like Uncle Noah.

67
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,467
Mom.

68
00:04:07,067 --> 00:04:10,767
Sorry that you were bothered
by my reaction.

69
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:13,700
Thank you, sweetie.

70
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:17,667
- I love you, Mom.
- I love you, too!

71
00:04:18,567 --> 00:04:21,267
So that's why our youngest
was silent.

72
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,633
Are you okay now?

73
00:04:22,767 --> 00:04:24,867
I'm all good, bro.

74
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,933
Here's a serious question, Mom.

75
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:28,967
Are you and Uncle Noah getting
married soon?

76
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:31,933
- What?
- Oh my!

77
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:35,367
Why are you asking about
marriage so soon?

78
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:36,833
No, I want to ask you to wait

79
00:04:36,967 --> 00:04:38,600
until Daisy and I get
back together.

80
00:04:38,733 --> 00:04:40,133
So we can have a double wedding.
It'll save us a lot.

81
00:04:40,267 --> 00:04:40,967
Gosh!

82
00:04:42,167 --> 00:04:43,267
I'm serious.

83
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:44,900
So that I don't have
to spend money.

84
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:46,900
You know what's cheaper?

85
00:04:48,133 --> 00:04:49,133
Triple wedding.

86
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,933
Let's wait for Andrea...

87
00:04:51,067 --> 00:04:52,233
- to get a boyfriend.
- Nice!

88
00:04:53,133 --> 00:04:55,033
Triple wedding, more economical!
Let's do it all at once.

89
00:04:56,333 --> 00:04:57,933
- No?
- That's so funny.

90
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:00,233
Don't get me involved.
I'm happy now.

91
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,433
Look at me. I'm so happy.

92
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:03,233
Come on!

93
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:05,233
God, you're
talking too much.

94
00:05:05,367 --> 00:05:06,733
Thank you, my dear children.

95
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,833
<i> I need to be vigilant.</i>

96
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:30,200
I need to know everything about
my husband.

97
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:48,933
Manuel!

98
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,533
Hazel,

99
00:07:57,067 --> 00:07:58,367
did you go through
my things?

100
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,100
I'm asking you. Answer me.

101
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,467
Are you looking for this?

102
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:27,233
Why do you have that?

103
00:08:38,233 --> 00:08:39,633
Why did you burn it?

104
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,733
This is the only memory
I have left of them!

105
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:46,633
Because that's what
it should be.

106
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:49,233
The nerve of you.

107
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,100
Did you really have to do it in
my house?

108
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,900
You're keeping your trash
in here.

109
00:08:58,067 --> 00:09:00,633
Hazel, this is the only memory
I have of them!

110
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:06,633
Then, good.

111
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:11,767
I no longer have to look
for something to burn.

112
00:09:23,367 --> 00:09:25,367
You're so evil!

113
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,833
You're so evil, Hazel!

114
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,800
That's why it's so difficult
to love you!

115
00:09:41,433 --> 00:09:42,667
What did you say?

116
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,200
You're so difficult to love!

117
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:51,167
- Darn you!
- Hazel!

118
00:09:52,933 --> 00:09:53,900
- Animal!
- Stop!

119
00:09:54,033 --> 00:09:54,967
Animal!

120
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:09,133
Darn you, Manuel?

121
00:10:14,900 --> 00:10:16,133
Manuel?

122
00:10:16,567 --> 00:10:17,567
Manuel?

123
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:21,933
Manuel!

124
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:23,867
I didn't...

125
00:10:24,733 --> 00:10:26,133
Manuel, I didn't mean it.

126
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:27,500
Manuel.

127
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:34,067
Manuel.

128
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:34,733
Wait.

129
00:10:35,233 --> 00:10:36,700
I'll take you to the hospital.

130
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:38,133
No, don't touch me!

131
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:39,967
I didn't mean it.

132
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:41,900
- Wait, wait!
- You didn't mean it?

133
00:10:42,467 --> 00:10:45,400
- Hold on. Wait.
- Mom! Dad!

134
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:48,100
Mom, what did you do to Dad?

135
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:48,933
Nothing...

136
00:10:49,067 --> 00:10:50,700
- Dad!
- No, I didn't mean it!

137
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,567
What are you saying? You did it
on purpose!

138
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:54,333
You wanted to hurt me!

139
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:57,567
You've been hurting me
even before.

140
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,167
This isn't the first time!

141
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:04,367
Hazel, I'm so tired of this!

142
00:11:06,067 --> 00:11:08,333
You do nothing but control
my life.

143
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,833
And get jealous about
my first family.

144
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:14,767
You even burned the only memory
I have left of them!

145
00:11:15,667 --> 00:11:17,567
I'm so sick of this!

146
00:11:18,967 --> 00:11:21,033
We'd better get a divorce!

147
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:23,633
Dad!

148
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:24,933
Dad!

149
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,400
Dad!

150
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:38,533
You're going to divorce me?

151
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:41,267
You're going to divorce me?

152
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,000
Fine!

153
00:11:44,500 --> 00:11:45,333
Go ahead!

154
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:46,767
I dare you!

155
00:11:46,900 --> 00:11:48,100
Wait! Wait!

156
00:11:48,233 --> 00:11:50,833
Wait, no, no. How did this turn
into a separation?

157
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:52,467
- Dad!
- Dear.

158
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:54,033
Dear, I'm sorry.

159
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:57,600
I can't take your mom anymore.
I'd better leave.

160
00:11:57,733 --> 00:11:59,500
No, Dad. I'm coming with you.

161
00:11:59,633 --> 00:12:00,500
No!

162
00:12:00,633 --> 00:12:01,500
What do you mean by
I'm coming with you?

163
00:12:01,633 --> 00:12:02,767
You're not going anywhere.
You stay here,

164
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:03,667
- Jessica!
- No!

165
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,333
- You stay...
- I want to be with Dad!

166
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:09,033
And where would you live?

167
00:12:09,167 --> 00:12:10,567
Where would you
and your dad live?

168
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,600
On the streets?

169
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:14,433
What will he feed you? Scrubs
from the trash?

170
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:17,300
You're dad relies on me, too.
Do you forget that?

171
00:12:17,433 --> 00:12:20,033
You really think so little
of Dad, Mommy!

172
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:22,900
Dad, when are we leaving?

173
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:24,067
I said no!

174
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,600
You're staying here!

175
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:27,700
You're not leaving! You will
stay here, Jessica!

176
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:29,200
- Let go!
- You stay here!

177
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:30,867
And that's final!

178
00:12:39,067 --> 00:12:40,900
Dear, I'm the only one leaving.

179
00:12:41,567 --> 00:12:42,533
You stay here.

180
00:12:43,067 --> 00:12:44,067
No, Dad.

181
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,867
I'll only stay in this house
if you're here.

182
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:49,133
But if you leave, I'm leaving,
too.

183
00:12:49,567 --> 00:12:52,200
Dear, stay here.
Stay with your mom.

184
00:12:53,633 --> 00:12:55,100
Your life's here.

185
00:12:55,667 --> 00:12:57,567
Everything you need is here.

186
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:02,167
Your school,
your comfortable life.

187
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,133
It's with your mom.

188
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:05,567
Your mom can give it to you.

189
00:13:05,700 --> 00:13:08,300
Dear, I'll be honest with you.
I can't support you yet.

190
00:13:08,433 --> 00:13:10,333
Your mom is right.

191
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,267
This is the first time
I'm asking you a favor.

192
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,367
Please listen to me.

193
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:22,333
Don't worry.

194
00:13:23,067 --> 00:13:25,667
Once I'm ready, I'll get you.

195
00:13:31,733 --> 00:13:32,767
Dad.

196
00:13:32,900 --> 00:13:35,500
Let's tend to your wound, Dad.

197
00:13:38,367 --> 00:13:39,233
Dad.

198
00:13:47,133 --> 00:13:50,000
My lawyer has already executed
the affidavit of complaint.

199
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:52,500
Okay, Uncle.

200
00:13:52,633 --> 00:13:56,300
I'll talk to Daisy's
neighbors to testify in court.

201
00:13:56,467 --> 00:13:59,067
I'll make sure Lance remains
in jail.

202
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,667
I will help you as much
as I can.

203
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,000
Thank you, Uncle.

204
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:12,633
Uncle, thank you for saving
my life.

205
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:14,633
I owe you my life.

206
00:14:15,833 --> 00:14:17,033
Come on. Don't mention it.

207
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:23,467
Once I've fixed things with
my family,

208
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,600
I won't have as much time
for Mom.

209
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:30,433
Maybe you could look
after her instead?

210
00:14:32,433 --> 00:14:33,600
Don't worry, Jeffrey.

211
00:14:34,467 --> 00:14:37,000
I will take care of her
for the rest of her life.

212
00:14:37,567 --> 00:14:39,000
I'll count on you.

213
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:41,067
Uncle, I'll get going.

214
00:14:41,667 --> 00:14:42,533
Be safe.

215
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:45,567
- You're leaving?
- Yes, Mom.

216
00:14:45,700 --> 00:14:47,167
I have to go somewhere.

217
00:14:47,300 --> 00:14:48,667
Bye, Uncle.

218
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:49,700
Bye.

219
00:14:53,967 --> 00:14:55,633
What did Dr. Cortes say?

220
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,167
I didn't talk to him.

221
00:14:59,667 --> 00:15:04,533
I won't let you get discharged.
You're still under observation.

222
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:06,433
Felma, I'm okay.

223
00:15:06,933 --> 00:15:11,367
The more we stay here, the more
we're losing time.

224
00:15:12,133 --> 00:15:13,567
Don't be stubborn.

225
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,100
If you're worrying
about our business,

226
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:19,867
Andrea can handle that. She can
run the operations.

227
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:23,500
What about the launch
of Sisig Ni Bunso?

228
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,933
Your interview with Pinoy Moms?

229
00:15:26,067 --> 00:15:27,233
You worry about so many things.

230
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:29,800
Can we just take it slow?

231
00:15:30,167 --> 00:15:31,567
Maybe try to get better first?

232
00:15:32,233 --> 00:15:33,433
But, Felma...

233
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:35,400
You won't win against me.

234
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,200
I'm your boss.

235
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:47,267
Whatever you say, boss.

236
00:15:54,067 --> 00:15:55,933
This is a lot, Dad.

237
00:15:56,067 --> 00:15:58,967
- Is this all for me?
- Yes, that's all yours.

238
00:16:00,233 --> 00:16:01,733
Jeff, don't give her too much.

239
00:16:01,867 --> 00:16:03,700
You might spoil Tetay.

240
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,033
Let me do this.

241
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,867
I owe our daughter a lot.

242
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:17,067
I need to make it up to her.
Okay?

243
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:31,833
By the way, I've talked to
some of your neighbors.

244
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:36,333
I've convinced many of them
to testify against Lance.

245
00:16:36,467 --> 00:16:38,000
Thank you, Dad.

246
00:16:38,133 --> 00:16:40,067
I'll also file a case
against him.

247
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,833
Physical abuse
and grave threats.

248
00:16:42,833 --> 00:16:43,800
That's right.

249
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,300
Lance must pay for all the abuse
he put you through.

250
00:16:48,267 --> 00:16:51,333
Daisy, let me know if you
need help.

251
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:52,900
Okay?

252
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:53,767
I will.

253
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,000
Here's your favorite. Chicken.

254
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,133
Before I forget.

255
00:16:58,267 --> 00:17:01,633
Mom's inviting you into
our house this weekend.

256
00:17:01,767 --> 00:17:04,133
There will be a thanksgiving
dinner for Uncle Noah.

257
00:17:04,267 --> 00:17:05,733
Tetay, you will finally
your grandma.

258
00:17:06,267 --> 00:17:08,633
- Really, Dad?
- Yes. And your aunties, too.

259
00:17:10,033 --> 00:17:11,133
Yay!

260
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:12,033
Go on and eat.

261
00:17:12,167 --> 00:17:13,733
Here's some rice.

262
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:18,533
Manuel!

263
00:17:19,967 --> 00:17:20,933
Manuel, what's this?

264
00:17:21,733 --> 00:17:23,733
Don't tell me you're really
leaving?

265
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:27,600
I've already talked to Jessica.

266
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:29,500
She's not coming with me.

267
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:33,267
Should I thank you?

268
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:34,833
What?

269
00:17:35,367 --> 00:17:37,233
Can you really leave
your family?

270
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,500
You really are a worthless
husband.

271
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:45,500
Well, that's not surprising.

272
00:17:46,667 --> 00:17:48,767
You left your first family,
didn't you?

273
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:54,267
I left them because you forced
me to marry you!

274
00:17:54,900 --> 00:17:58,400
Are you telling me that
I trapped you into this?

275
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,633
If you leave,

276
00:18:05,333 --> 00:18:06,300
remember this...

277
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:11,900
you will never see Jessica
again if you leave.

278
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:15,633
Hazel,

279
00:18:16,767 --> 00:18:18,900
Jessica is my daughter. I have
the right to see her.

280
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:22,267
Or would you want to settle this
in the family court?

281
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:24,700
And then, let's go straight to
the Superior Court of Justice

282
00:18:24,833 --> 00:18:25,967
to file for a divorce?

283
00:18:43,900 --> 00:18:45,767
Dear, I'm sorry.

284
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:49,100
I can't take your mom anymore.

285
00:18:49,667 --> 00:18:51,433
We no longer get along.

286
00:18:52,800 --> 00:18:54,267
I've thought of it, Dad.

287
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:56,367
And I realized that...

288
00:18:57,967 --> 00:19:00,100
you're better off away from Mom.

289
00:19:00,533 --> 00:19:02,633
Dad, she hurt you.

290
00:19:03,167 --> 00:19:06,667
And if you stay,
it could even get worse.

291
00:19:07,833 --> 00:19:09,433
So I won't stop you anymore.

292
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:14,567
Always remember...

293
00:19:15,033 --> 00:19:16,433
that only your mom and I
will be separated.

294
00:19:16,567 --> 00:19:17,533
Not us.

295
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:21,167
I'm going to miss you.

296
00:19:24,433 --> 00:19:26,267
Come on, Dear.

297
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,733
It's as if we'll no longer
see each other again.

298
00:19:30,533 --> 00:19:32,833
Dad, it's not the same anymore.

299
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,967
You've always been here.

300
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,367
You wake us up in the morning.

301
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,367
You make our lunches.

302
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,233
You do the laundry,

303
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:48,300
even if I insist I can do it
myself.

304
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:52,433
Dad, you do the groceries.

305
00:19:52,767 --> 00:19:55,267
You take care of everything.

306
00:19:56,667 --> 00:19:57,833
You take care of us.

307
00:20:00,267 --> 00:20:01,167
Dear.

308
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,533
Come on, that's enough.

309
00:20:02,967 --> 00:20:03,867
Don't worry.

310
00:20:04,633 --> 00:20:06,600
Once I get a house,

311
00:20:06,733 --> 00:20:09,300
I'll do all those things for you
again when you visit.

312
00:20:10,033 --> 00:20:12,200
I love you, Dad.

313
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:14,367
Dad, don't leave me.

314
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:15,600
I love you, too, Dear.

315
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:20,133
Remember, your dad loves you
so much.

316
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:25,867
Manuel?

317
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:32,100
Manuel...

318
00:20:33,867 --> 00:20:34,967
Manuel?

319
00:20:36,267 --> 00:20:37,167
Please...

320
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:38,667
Please stay.

321
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:42,400
I'm ready to talk
about everything.

322
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,167
Let's fix this, Manuel.

323
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:50,167
I promise that I'll change.

324
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:52,700
I promise.

325
00:20:52,833 --> 00:20:53,433
Hazel.

326
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:55,933
You said it many times.

327
00:20:56,067 --> 00:20:57,200
But nothing changed!

328
00:20:57,333 --> 00:20:59,233
No, no.

329
00:20:59,367 --> 00:21:01,633
It'll be different this time.

330
00:21:01,767 --> 00:21:02,467
I promise...

331
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:04,067
- Manuel, no. Wait.
- Go on.

332
00:21:04,200 --> 00:21:05,100
- Manuel!
- Leave me be.

333
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:06,267
Don't leave me!

334
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:07,267
Manuel!

335
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:08,467
Manuel!

336
00:21:08,900 --> 00:21:10,033
Manuel!

337
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:12,733
Mom.

338
00:21:12,867 --> 00:21:14,500
Mom, let Dad go.

339
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:18,633
Manuel!

340
00:21:38,433 --> 00:21:39,567
He had the guts.

341
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:40,500
The nerve of him!

342
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:44,967
Take it easy, friend.

343
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:47,333
No.

344
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:48,933
He was so arrogant!

345
00:21:49,733 --> 00:21:52,733
As if he can live
on his meager salary.

346
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,033
Speaking of.

347
00:21:56,800 --> 00:21:58,700
If he's been working
behind your back,

348
00:21:59,533 --> 00:22:01,267
don't you think Manuel has saved

349
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:04,067
enough for him to get back
to the Philippines?

350
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:06,900
He can try.

351
00:22:08,967 --> 00:22:11,033
So, are you going to stop him?

352
00:22:11,567 --> 00:22:12,333
How?

353
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:15,133
You don't even know
where he is right now.

354
00:22:17,933 --> 00:22:18,600
Come on.

355
00:22:24,067 --> 00:22:25,533
Okay, you can use this.

356
00:22:28,300 --> 00:22:32,000
Thank you very much
Mr. and Mrs. Wilson,

357
00:22:32,333 --> 00:22:34,200
for letting me stay here.

358
00:22:35,133 --> 00:22:36,333
It'll be temporary.

359
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:37,800
Nonsense, Dear.

360
00:22:37,933 --> 00:22:39,600
We should be thanking you.

361
00:22:39,733 --> 00:22:42,167
We were wanting someone
to stay here with us.

362
00:22:42,533 --> 00:22:44,633
And you're welcome
as long as you need.

363
00:22:44,767 --> 00:22:46,433
That's all right, son.

364
00:22:46,567 --> 00:22:48,767
The neighborhood's not as safe
as it used to be.

365
00:22:49,567 --> 00:22:51,200
A lot of break-ins lately.

366
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:55,300
As well, we're not as quick
on our feet as before.

367
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:57,867
And we can use some
company around here.

368
00:22:59,267 --> 00:23:00,767
Think about it, Manuel.

369
00:23:01,800 --> 00:23:02,500
Okay.

370
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:07,100
I will think about it,
Sir, Ma'am.

371
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:13,467
You know, I promised my daughter
I'll have my own house

372
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,833
so she can visit me.

373
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:19,233
Jessica is more than welcome
to visit you any time.

374
00:23:19,367 --> 00:23:20,233
Okay, okay.

375
00:23:20,367 --> 00:23:24,333
But can I think about it first?

376
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:29,967
Because, you know,
I also want my own house.

377
00:23:30,100 --> 00:23:32,067
- Of course, of course.
- We understand. We understand.

378
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:34,700
We'll leave you
so you can get settled.

379
00:23:35,200 --> 00:23:36,600
We'll just be around.

380
00:23:37,167 --> 00:23:37,833
Thank you.

381
00:23:49,267 --> 00:23:50,667
Mom, what's going on?

382
00:23:53,733 --> 00:23:54,400
Nothing.

383
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:59,567
I'm used to having
my clothes ready.

384
00:24:00,633 --> 00:24:01,533
And that I have clean clothes.

385
00:24:01,667 --> 00:24:02,300
And now...

386
00:24:04,867 --> 00:24:06,833
I don't even have a clean
uniform.

387
00:24:06,967 --> 00:24:10,933
When your dad was here, he
always took care of that.

388
00:24:13,600 --> 00:24:15,167
I'm sorry, Mom.

389
00:24:15,300 --> 00:24:16,700
I was supposed to do
the laundry,

390
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:18,567
but I had a school project

391
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,167
- to finish.
- No, no, no.

392
00:24:21,133 --> 00:24:22,300
It's not your fault.

393
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:25,333
I only got used to your dad
being here.

394
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:29,333
When he's here, he took care of
everything in the house.

395
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:31,867
But he's no longer here
because...

396
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:35,567
Because of Felma!

397
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:37,700
You're a mistress! Mistress!

398
00:24:37,833 --> 00:24:38,700
Here's the mistress!

399
00:24:38,833 --> 00:24:41,033
Are we already running out
of men?

400
00:24:41,167 --> 00:24:43,100
That's why you're stealing
someone else's husband?

401
00:24:43,233 --> 00:24:44,233
I'm not a mistress!

402
00:24:44,367 --> 00:24:45,100
- What do you mean you're not?
- You're a mistress!

403
00:24:45,233 --> 00:24:46,300
Mistress! Mistress!
There she is!

404
00:24:46,433 --> 00:24:47,233
There's the mistress!

405
00:24:47,367 --> 00:24:48,433
Felma is not my mistress!
You know that!

406
00:24:48,567 --> 00:24:49,200
There she is!

407
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:51,233
- Stop it!
- Ouch!

408
00:24:51,467 --> 00:24:52,800
Brace yourself, you snake.

409
00:24:57,233 --> 00:24:58,700
Felma Ruiz.

410
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:02,600
Do you think I can't find you?

411
00:25:03,567 --> 00:25:05,000
Mom, what are you going to do?

412
00:25:05,733 --> 00:25:06,667
Do you see this video?

413
00:25:07,233 --> 00:25:08,100
- What's that?
- This is the video

414
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:11,333
when I caught your dad
with Felma.

415
00:25:11,467 --> 00:25:12,700
Wait, what are you
going to do with it?

416
00:25:12,833 --> 00:25:14,167
You're not posting that,
are you?

417
00:25:14,300 --> 00:25:15,633
Yes, I am.

418
00:25:15,767 --> 00:25:18,500
I want the world to know
how flirtatious Felma is!

419
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:19,667
Mom, give it to me.

420
00:25:19,800 --> 00:25:20,933
Mom!

421
00:25:21,833 --> 00:25:22,767
Too late.

422
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:34,767
I entered this relationship
wanting to marry you.

423
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:36,033
Will you marry me?

424
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,533
Mom's losing it, Dad.

425
00:25:37,667 --> 00:25:41,433
She posted your video
at the park on the FMP website.

426
00:25:41,567 --> 00:25:43,067
The nerve of you!

427
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:43,867
I'm not a mistress!

428
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,067
There she is! The mistress!

429
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:46,133
Call the PR team.

430
00:25:46,267 --> 00:25:47,900
We need damage control ASAP.

431
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:49,667
And tell them to take it down.

432
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:53,800
Just ignore our classmates
who bash and bully you.

433
00:25:53,933 --> 00:25:55,800
What if it's your mom
who gets bashed online,

434
00:25:55,933 --> 00:25:56,833
and you get bullied
because of it?

435
00:25:56,967 --> 00:25:58,533
Do you know how painful that is?

436
00:25:58,667 --> 00:26:00,767
Mom, do you want me to go
to Coleen's school instead?

437
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:02,067
What will you do there?

438
00:26:02,533 --> 00:26:04,000
Will you bully her classmates
like they do to your sister?

439
00:26:04,133 --> 00:26:06,233
That will make Coleen even less
likely to go to school.

440
00:26:06,367 --> 00:26:08,467
I know that it was your wife,
that home wrecker and monster,

441
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,567
who spread Mom's video.

442
00:26:09,733 --> 00:26:11,433
Have mercy on us.

443
00:26:11,567 --> 00:26:12,800
We're living peacefully.

444
00:26:12,933 --> 00:26:14,700
Leave us in peace.

445
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:16,733
- Help!
- Be quiet or I'll shoot!

446
00:26:16,867 --> 00:26:17,767
Hey!

447
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:24,100
I'm calling the police!

448
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,400
Manuel!

449
00:26:27,533 --> 00:26:29,233
Manuel!
